# === ALLOWLIST STRATEGY ===
# Ignore EVERYTHING by default, then explicitly un-ignore only the files we want.
# This makes "git add ." completely safe.

# Ignore all files and folders
*

# === ALLOW THESE SPECIFIC FILES ===
!.gitignore
!compling26_assignment (1).ipynb
!*.pdf

# === RE-IGNORE SPECIFIC FILES ===
kimi-export-*.md
compling26_assignment (1).py

# === DIRECTORIES THAT MUST NEVER BE COMMITTED ===
.claude/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
__pycache__/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# === FILE TYPES THAT MUST NEVER BE COMMITTED ===
*.pkl
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.h5
*.npy
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
*.md
